te is one of it\'s biggestÂ accomplishments, which, in a more personal level, a critique of where the field of design is leading to; away for the principal of functionality and simplicity by which it was founded and by which it can still be justified.','theJSJ v3.0','','private','closed','closed','','thejsj-v3-0','','','2012-10-25 11:55:27','2012-10-25 11:55:27','',0,'http://thejsj.com/?post_type=piece&#038;p=77',8,'piece','',0),(78,1,'2011-08-19 19:41:12','2011-08-19 19:41:12','','Portfolio - The JSJ','','inherit','open','open','','portfolio-the-jsj','','','2011-08-19 19:41:12','2011-08-19 19:41:12','',77,'http://thejsj.com/newportfolio/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Portfolio-The-JSJ.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(79,1,'2011-08-19 19:47:28','2011-08-19 19:47:28','Site designed for the Iberoamerican Leadership Congress 2011 held in Puerto Rico.\r\n\r\nThe site as designed mostly as a portal for information related to the congress. This is mainly a content site and was designed accordingly (through it\'s horizontallity, through it\'s white background and typography). The experience is designed for the user to read. Social Media was also integrated to promote the congress among it\'s visitros.\r\n\r\nThe design is based on the previous logo design. The pallette utilizes diffrentÂ flavos ofÂ blue to contrast elements in the page. Also diffrent shades of gray were used and incoporated almost as a fade of the dominant blue background. This type of light gray was used mostly to differentiate diffrent spaces in the page. The menu typography is also very intresting in how it was utilized as a way to mark both, the professional aspect of the conferencas as well as the youth of it\'s participants.\r\n\r\n<em>This site will be launched very shortly and is on the final stages of it\'s design.</em>','Iberoamerican Leadership Congress.org','','private','closed','closed','','iberoamerican-leadership-congress-org-2','','','2012-10-25 11:55:27','2012-10-25 11:55:27','',0,'http://thejsj.com/?post_type=piece&#038;p=79',2,'piece','',0),(80,1,'2011-08-19 19:49:09','2011-08-19 19:49:09','This website was done for a the Chatka Summer camp.\r\n\r\nThe site is a very simple site, done over a year ago. The site is a basic presentation site for the camp. Because of this a very simple layout was used. The design was a combination of a redesign, taking some of the features used in the previous site and new ideas. The aesthethics of the site reference the camp brand and logo (dark yellos, light browns) while making use of the \'outdoors\' present in previous design and very portinent for this type of summer camp.\r\n\r\nThe site employs Jquery technology for galleries and tabs, animated GIFS for the menus, Flickr embeddeds and simple HTML.','ChatkaCamp.org','','draft','closed','closed','','chatkacamp-org','','','2012-10-25 11:55:11','2012-10-25 11:55:11','',0,'http://thejsj.com/?post_type=piece&#038;p=80',29,'piece','',0),(81,1,'2011-08-19 19:48:57','2011-08-19 19:48:57','','www.chatkacamp.org','','inherit','open','open','','www-chatkacamp-org','','','2011-08-19 19:48:57','2011-08-19 19:48:57','',80,'http://thejsj.com/newportfolio/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/www.chatkacamp.org_.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(82,1,'2011-08-19 19:52:19','2011-08-19 19:52:19','Website done for InterLeacroft, a proyect established in 2009 to launch and promote the Romanization of Intellectual Property.\r\n\r\nFor this emerging and daring undertaking, a website was created to showcase and present the institution and it\'s ideas. As such, the sites presents what the institution does, serves as a platform for trainings and courses and for spreading the ideas of this proposition thru the intituion\'s blog.\r\n\r\nIn terms of design, the image of the instituion was considered at all times. The pallette and typography utilized, both in the website and in the logo, serve to show the balance between the innovation inspired by what the proyect proposes and the formality intertwin