 21:54:20','2011-09-23 21:54:20','mfa blog','MFA Blog','','inherit','open','open','','138-revision-2','','','2011-09-23 21:54:20','2011-09-23 21:54:20','',138,'http://thejsj.com/2011/138-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(403,1,'2012-02-13 04:21:51','2012-02-13 04:21:51','','Final Book - No Cover','','inherit','open','open','','final-book-no-cover-2','','','2012-02-13 04:21:51','2012-02-13 04:21:51','',320,'http://thejsj.com/newportfolio/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/Final-Book-No-Cover.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(317,1,'2012-01-07 19:52:11','2012-01-07 19:52:11','This paper is the proposal for the Final Presentation on my Graduate Semintar, here at VCU.\n\n<a href=\"http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/SEMINAR-PAPER-IDEAS.pdf\">Download as a PDF(Recomended)</a>\n\n<em>âThe thing with Processing is that it looks like Processingâ âThe Thing with ________ is that it looks like ________â</em>\n\nI heard this quote the other day at our seminar class from one of our classmates. That stuck me. Is there something wrong with <em>something </em>looking like <em>something</em>. After some thought, I developed my own MAD LIPS statement to excercise my own thoughts. âThe thing with _________ (insert art form here) is that it looks like __________ (insert art form here)â. âThe thing with painting is that it looks like paintingâ. âThe thing with bronze is that is looks like bronzeâ. âThe thing with letterpress is that it looks like letterpressâ. âThe thing with guitars is that it sounds like guitarsâ. Yet, we donât see painters running for their lives, Picasso tumbling on his grave, or Rodin being forgotten as a great sculptor. Artists ow a lot to their tools and they have a deep relation to them. Many great artists emerge from the superb understanding and skill they acquire with their tools and this is something not to be frowned upon. For this work I want to explore the relationship between the artist and his tools and his medium. How should we view this relationship?\n\n<em>Color as a tool, Color as a Medium</em>\n\nFor this work, I also want to explore the subject of color within this theoretical framework and within these questions. Is color a medium or a tool? What is the relationship between the tool and the medium? How have different views of color as tool/medium affected the work of artists in different fields?\n\n<em>From Tool to Medium: The Computer</em>\n\nAnother field of interest for me is the changing role of the computer from tool to medium. Many present day artists work exclusively on the computer and what is produced with it is the end in itself, rather than being a tool to facilitate manual work. What exactly do we mean by saying that the computer is a medium rather than a tool? What changes caused this? Is this even appropriate to say?\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','The Artist, Writer and Musician: Their Relationship to their tools.','','inherit','open','open','','218-autosave','','','2012-01-07 19:52:11','2012-01-07 19:52:11','',218,'http://thejsj.com/2012/218-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(318,1,'2011-11-01 02:08:06','2011-11-01 02:08:06','This paper is the proposal for the Final Presentation on my Graduate Semintar, here at VCU.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/SEMINAR-PAPER-IDEAS.pdf\">Download as a PDF(Recomended)</a>\r\n\r\n<em>âThe thing with Processing is that it looks like Processingâ âThe Thing with ________ is that it looks like ________â</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI heard this quote the other day at our seminar class from one of our classmates. That stuck me. Is there something wrong with <em>something </em>looking like <em>something</em>. After some thought, I developed my own MAD LIPS statement to excercise my own thoughts. âThe thing with _________ (insert art form here) is that it looks like __________ (insert art form here)â. âThe thing with painting is that it looks like paintingâ. âThe thing with bronze is that is looks like bronzeâ. âThe thing with letterpress is that it looks like letterpressâ. âThe thing with guitars is that it sounds like guitarsâ. Yet, we donât see painters running for their lives, Picasso tumbling on his grave, or Rodin being forgotten as a great sculptor. Artists ow a lot to their tools and they have a deep relation to them. Many great artists emerge from the superb understanding and skill they acquire with their tools and this is something not to be frowned upon. For this work I want to explore the relationship between the artist and his tools and his medium. How should we view this relationship?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>Color as a tool, Color as a Medium</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFor this work, I also want to explore the subject of color within this theoretical framework and within these questions. Is color a medium or a tool? What is the relationship between the tool and the medium? How have different views of color as tool/medium affected the work of artists in different fields?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>From Tool to Medium: The Computer</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAnother field of interest for me is the changing role of the computer from tool to medium. Many present day artists work exclusively on the computer and what is produced with it is the end in itself, rather than being a tool to facilitate manual work. What exactly do we mean by saying that the computer is a medium rather than a tool? What changes caused this? Is this even appropriate to say?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','The Artist, Writer and Musician: Their Relationship to their tools.','','inherit','open','open','','218-revision-4','','','2011-11-01 02:08:06','2011-11-01 02:08:06','',218,'http://thejsj.com/2011/218-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(321,1,'2011-11-09 06:26:41','2011-11-09 06:26:41','[gallery link=\"file\" ids=\"322,323,324,325,326,327,328,329\"]\r\n\r\n\"Random Trends\" Â is a project done for my MFA data visualization class. Through this project I was able to analyze different strings of numbers as random information and give them a visual language that made it simple to see easily see patterns between them. Rather than see this as a \"poster design\" or something similar, I thought of it more as a new language of visualizing numerical information. Through this other way of visualizingÂ informationÂ about changes (temperature, binary code, financial indexes), we can start seeing graphic design as a tool for analyzing data.','Random Trends','','publish','closed','closed','','random-trends','','','2013-05-30 18:55:07','2013-05-30 18:55:07','',0,'http://thejsj.com/?post_type=piece&#038;p=321',12,'piece','',0),(1219,1,'2013-02-02 21:27:43','2013-02-02 21:27:43','','IMG_1385_2','','inherit','open','open','','img_1385_2','','','2013-02-02 21:27:43','2013-02-02 21:27:43','',1187,'http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/IMG_1385_2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1220,1,'2013-02-02 21:27:45','2013-02-02 21:27:45','','IMG_1391_2','','inherit','open','open','','img_1391_2','','','2013-02-02 21:27:45','2013-02-02 21:27:45','',1187,'http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/IMG_1391_2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1228,1,'2013-02-02 21:28:00','2013-02-02 21:28:00','','IMG_9520','','inherit','open','open','','img_9520','','','2013-02-02 21:28:00','2013-02-02 21:28:00','',1187,'http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/IMG_9520.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1229,1,'2013-02-02 21:28:02','2013-02-02 21:28:02','','IMG_9538','','inherit','open','open','','img_9538','','','2013-02-02 21:28:02','2013-02-02 21:28:02','',1187,'http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/IMG_9538.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1230,1,'2013-02-02 21:28:04','2013-02-02 21:28:04','','IMG_9540','','inherit','open','open','','img_9540','','','2013-02-02 21:28:04','2013-02-02 21:28:04','',1187,'http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/upload