\"http://vimeo.com/askyourself\">Fifty People, One Question</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n\r\nWhere do you wish to wake up? \r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/2834087\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe> <p><a href=\"http://vimeo.com/2834087\">Fifty People, One Question: London</a> from <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/askyourself\">Fifty People, One Question</a> on <a href=\"http://vimeo.com\">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n','Videos: People On the Street','','inherit','open','open','','1165-revision-4','','','2013-01-28 23:42:02','2013-01-28 23:42:02','',1165,'http://thejsj.com/uncategorized/1165-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(1170,1,'2013-01-29 01:09:14','2013-01-29 01:09:14','','Cv - Jorge Silva-Jetter','','inherit','open','open','','cv-jorge-silva-jetter','','','2013-01-29 01:09:14','2013-01-29 01:09:14','',4,'http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Cv-Jorge-Silva-Jetter.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(357,1,'2011-11-01 03:49:33','2011-11-01 03:49:33','<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/mBCiKqyzH9U\" height=\"400\" width=\"600\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nThis interactive piece is a time-line of 60 years and 80+ events of the life and work of Richard Serra. The intention of the time-line is to make all information easily and quickly accessible, where the interface is as invisible as possible, and everything can be zoomed in and out to create an intuitive, user-friendly experience while not sacrificing on the amount of information give.\r\n\r\nZoom becomes the principal means of navigation and the ease of zooming in this interaction makes all the nodes easily accessible. Also, because there is a vast space to be covered, every X position of the mouse has a specific X position in the graph. In this way, the whole span of the time-line can be navigated by just moving the mouse form one side of the screen to another. Again, the time-line is immediately accessed through the X position of the mouse. The same occurs with the Y position, in which every particular Y position has it corresponding Y position in the time-line by which all the information can be accessed by vertically moving the mouse.\r\n\r\nThis piece gains particular relevance in a world with overflowing information. This overflow of information leads to condensation, editing, simplification, or difficulty in navigation. This piece aspires to have both: Vast amounts of information with ease and quickness of navigation. The format could possibly be used, not only for a time-line, but for many other types of information architecture.\r\n\r\n<h3>Download the App for Mac:</h3>\r\nYou can download the complete application (exported through Processing) and use it yourself. This is recomendable for a fully functional and seamless experience.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Richard-Serra-Interactive-Timeline-Mac.zip\">Richard Serra Interactive Timeline - Mac</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Richard-Serra-Interactive-Timeline-Windows.zip\">Richard Serra Interactive Timeline - Windows</a>Â (Currently not tested)\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Richard-Serra-Interactive-Timline-Linux.zip\">Richard Serra Interactive Timline - Linux</a>Â (Currently not tested)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Richard Serra: A Time-line','','publish','closed','closed','','richard-serra-a-time-line','','','2013-10-19 04:25:04','2013-10-19 04:25:04','',0,'http://thejsj.com/?post_type=piece&#038;p=357',11,'piece','',0),(510,1,'2012-03-18 21:10:29','2012-03-18 21:10:29','This is a short essay of what I intend to do with for my MFA thesis next years. It might be a little disorganized but it reflects the difficulty of pinning down on what I want to be about...\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Thesis-Writing-March-