Roma did for thousands of years. Inscribed into my monument will be the words âA Monument to the Roma, A people in movementâ.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, merely by accident, my giant piece of was will grow a wick, turning this endearing monument into a more common object, a candle; A candle made monumental by itâs scale. More unfortunate is the possibly that this beautiful and simple monument might be mysteriously lit.</blockquote>\r\nThis project was realized as part of my graduate workshop, in Spring 2012. The goal of the project was to study, understand and immerseÂ yourselfÂ in a specific culture. I chose the Roma, also know as Gypsies because of my longÂ fascinationÂ with their culture, music and way of life.\r\n\r\nOne of the goals of this project was to build a monument to this culture. I created a nomadic monument, a monument that would destroy itself and through this process question the nature of the monument as a creation of cultures tied to a specific place, but possibly alien to a nomadic culture such as the Roma, spread through out the world.\r\n\r\nThrough this project, I ventured the treacherousÂ waters of the moving image, sculpture and plural participation.','Monument to the Roma','','publish','closed','closed','','monument-to-the-roma','','','2013-05-30 18:58:03','2013-05-30 18:58:03','',0,'http://thejsj.com/?post_type=piece&#038;p=807',13,'piece','',0),(794,1,'2012-07-12 01:42:13','2012-07-12 01:42:13','I have done it!\n\n<a title=\"JSJ\'s NYClean\" href=\"javascript:(function() {window.location=window.location.toString().replace(/[?]{1}.*/,&quot;#$%^*()/*&gt;&lt;{}|\\:;`~\'\'~?nice=yeah&amp;author=thejsj&quot;);})()\">JSJ\'s NYClean</a>\n&nbsp;\n\nAfter a few days of tinkering around with a New York Time\'s fee wall, bookmarklets, urls and a little javascript I was able to figure out a way out of the pay wall in a way that\'s clean and efficient. This bookmarklet simply refreshes your page to remove the wall through hampering with your url a lit