es function calls the router\r\n\r\n6. The router redirects the app to search funciton, feeding it the query variable\r\n\r\n7. A query to the API is made and returned\r\n\r\n8. A collection is made\r\n\r\n9. That collection is rendered, appended to the html and binded\r\n\r\nOn a later episode of this great blog, I will talk a bit more about collections, models and a bit more about views. In the mean time, you can <a href=\"http://thejsj.com/2013/pugalicious/\">checkout this app</a> and checkout <a href=\"https://github.com/thejsj/clickOnJorge\">the repo on github.com</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Pugalicious - A Backbone App','','inherit','open','open','','1545-revision-v1','','','2013-10-09 04:27:23','2013-10-09 04:27:23','',1545,'http://thejsj.com/uncategorized/1545-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1573,1,'2013-10-09 04:47:58','2013-10-09 04:47:58','[gallery ids=\"1576,1577,1578,1575,1579,1581,1574\"]\r\n\r\nClickOnJorge is a simple game made around the wonderful Jorge (Yes, myself!). Â The user has 20 seconds to Â click on the highlighted Jorge as many time as possible. If he gets a high score, he gets to be on the high-scores page.\r\n<h3>How it Works</h3>\r\nAfter logging in, the decide how fast the game will be and how many blocks there will be. This determines difficulty and thus, the way score will be determined.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/coj2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1575\" alt=\"coj2\" src=\"http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/coj2-1024x669.jpg\" width=\"614\" height=\"401\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe user has 20 seconds to Â click on the highlighted Jorge as many time as possible.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/instructions.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1584\" alt=\"instructions\" src=\"http://thejsj.com/portfolio/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/instructions.png\" width=\"244\" height=\"218\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe highlighted blo